</para>
<para id="element-9">Suffix "1" and "2" refer to the two colliding bodies, whereas suffix "i" and "f"  refer to the "initial" and "final" states (before and after) of the collision respectively. It is important to visualize that two bodies will collide when their trajectory is such that the physical dimension of the bodies overlap. Further, one of the bodies approaches second body with greater speed (
<m:math>
<m:msub>
<m:mi> v </m:mi>
<m:mi> 1i </m:mi>
</m:msub>
<m:mo> &gt; </m:mo>
<m:msub>
