<m:mi> 2i </m:mi>
</m:msub>
</m:math>
) for collision to occur. In the figure above, two bodies are shown to have parallel trajectories so that body "A" does not strike "B" head on, but glances to move in different directions after collision.
</para>
<para id="element-10">Generally, the body with greater velocity that collides with another body is conventionally termed as "projectile" and the body which is hit is termed as "target".
</para>
<para id="element-11">
We must understand that the law of conservation of linear momentum is valid for a closed system, wherein there is no exchange of mass between the system and its surrounding. Also, we must note that above mathematical construct is a vector equation. This can be expressed in component form as :
